{"type":"message","id":"daa91f29","parentId":"e0386fe7","timestamp":"2026-02-15T18:04:50.526Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 20:04 GMT+2] OPERATION: RUST FORSAGE, HTTPX SNIPER & SECURITY AUDITOR.\n\n1.  **Rust Forsage (Core Logic):**\n    *   *Code:* Add `evaluate_skin_deal(price: f64, float: f64, pattern: u32) -> bool` to `src/rust_core/src/lib.rs`.\n    *   *Build:* `maturin develop` or `cargo build --release` (in container context).\n    *   *Benchmark:* Create `tests/perf/rust_vs_python.py`. Compare 1M evaluations.\n\n2.  **Network Sniper (HTTPX + HTTP/2):**\n    *   *Refactor:* Replace `aiohttp` with `httpx` in `src/dmarket/api/client.py`.\n    *   *Config:* Enable `http2=True`. Use Singleton `httpx.AsyncClient`.\n    *   *Watchdog:* Run `pytest tests/integration` and fix broken mocks/calls.\n\n3.  **Security Auditor (Deep Scan):**\n    *   *Orchestration:* `skill_orchestrator.dispatch(\"security_audit\")`.\n    *   *Tools:* Run `gitleaks`, `bandit`, `shellcheck`.\n    *   *Memory:* Check `/dev/shm` (Linux) or Windows Handles for leaks. Create cleanup logic.\n    *   *Fix:* Auto-patch any findings.\n\n4.  **Output:**\n    *   Benchmark Table (Rust vs Python).\n    *   HTTPX Refactor Stats (Files changed, Watchdog fixes).\n    *   Security Report (Vulns found/fixed).\n    *   Commit Hash."}],"timestamp":1771178690524}}
